<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I agree with the last post...<br>
From what I have heard from players and in forums, you need int, and wis for two different reasons when advancing in trade skills.<br>
One helps you to increase your skill faster, and one helps you to suceed more.<br>
The big thing is choosing hehe. On one hand, you will increase your skill faster. Your skill can go up a lvl even on a failure, so is it worth the pp to you to just dump it all into fast lvl increases?? Or do you hindure your failure rate, and chance it that you will be at the same skill lvl for longer??? (which in my opinoin gives you more chances to fail anyway.)As for charisma, that only helps with the purchase of components, and the selling if you sell it back to a merchant. So if you are patient enough, that jewelry can be changed between the time that you sell, and the time that you make your item, and then changed back again.<p>

<br>
Sorry to ramble, but that theory was hard to put into clear wording hehe.<hr>Gwyndolin Fireblade<br>
Elven Sisterhood<br>
Xegony server</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
