<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Brewbane, you are right in one aspect. But not the other. <p>

<br>
Now, as far as succeses go... Verant uses the HIGHEST of the two scores (int or wis). But not both, not for INCREASE in skill checks, not for success rates. If I have an Erudite Wizard that is fletching, he would not go up in skill to Master (105) in under an hour. My skill was at 0 when I started. Now in this case... I have a 207 int. And a 99 wis. Now with this in mind... I should not have gotten my skill to 105 in that short of a time (if wisdom was used as a increase in skill modifier). <p>

Now with the NEW patch... here is the way things go now... INT + STR. So now if you want to get better at ... smithing for example (already a pain in the ass) you need strenth items again and a good intelligence as well. Now with a 207 INT and a 77 STR (OUCH) I am getting now a severe penalty to my check for success let alone improvement. So I would suggest getting some of the better STR and INT items to go ahead and work on any skill. <p>

Also I need to mention, with the ACTUAL number that your INT and STR is... DO NOT let it be a prime number (a number that can only be divided by 1 and itself, like 199, or 133, which was used in an exaple from above). You will have MANY less successes and not go up in skill nearly as much. It messes up the formula for doing the work.<p>

<p>

This is my own thought and not IN GAME FORMULA.<p>

Why Verant brain farted and used STR for a check I'll never know... they shopuld have the relavant skill in this area... which would be Agility and dex, with a formula, lower number divided by the higher number to use as a modifier. So if you have a dex of 77 and agility of 77 the modifier would be one. Now a dex of 100 and a agi of 105... 105 divided by 100... gives a signaficantly better modifier... so the better the scores... and as long as there is a difference... the better the modifier... and if a skill is below 105 a penaly is applied to the modifier, to encourage better sts enhancement... and above 150 a bonus is applied... just my 2 cents how how it SHOULD be done...<hr>Orocular Goodheart<br>
Apprentice of Master Tashim<br>
Student of The Wyrd<br>
Keepers of Oak<br>
The Rathe</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
